medical_history.chief_complaint: Sudden onset of weakness in the right leg and paresthesiae in the dorsum of the right foot.
medical_history.history_of_present_illness: Symptoms began abruptly 2 hours prior to presentation during work as a housekeeper, characterized by a 'double tap' sound with each step on the right foot. No history of trauma. The patient has no habits that could aggravate the symptoms.
